Class App

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.application.Application
      • pl.edu.agh.jdziennik.App

  • public class App
extends javafx.application.Application
    Represents the application instance. This is the main class of the application (i.e. it contains main()). Object of this class holds references to other vital elements of the application.

      • getUser

        public WrappedTeacher getUser()
        Returns WrappedTeacher representing the current user. Should only be used in normal mode. Undefined behaviour when called in admin mode.
        Returns:
        the user

      • start

        public void start(javafx.stage.Stage primaryStage)
        for javafx Entry point of the GUI logic. Initializes the App object, shows user selection dialog and afterwards spawns application window in either admin or normal mode (depending on user choice).
